        <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">Australia, US</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n700 mb-3">Irreverent sarcasm, direct challenges. The humor hits hard and fast.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n500 italic">"Think you can beat the house? Cute."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-info/30 bg-info/5 p-5 shadow-sm">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-info bg-info/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mb-3">Understated</span>
        <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">UK</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n700 mb-3">Dry wit, knowing understatement. The humor is there if you're looking for it.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n500 italic">"The house edge doesn't care about your lucky shirt. But wear it if you like."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-n300/30 bg-white p-5 shadow-sm">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-n500 bg-n100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mb-3">Minimal</span>
        <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">Asia, Nordic</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n700 mb-3">Warm, clean, restrained. Written by someone with a sense of humor who chose restraint — not by a committee that never had one.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n500 italic">"Understanding the math behind each game helps you make better choices."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 id="the-directness-level">The directness level</h3>

    <p>
      How directly can you deliver hard truths?
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-6">
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-teal/30 bg-teal/5 p-5 shadow-sm">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-teal-dark bg-teal/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mb-3">Direct</span>
        <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">Australia, Nordic</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n700 mb-3">Plain facts, no softening. The reader gets the conclusion first and the evidence second.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n500 italic">"This bet is terrible. Here's why."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-info/30 bg-info/5 p-5 shadow-sm">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-info bg-info/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mb-3">Diplomatic</span>
        <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">UK, parts of Asia</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n700 mb-3">Same information, wrapped in comparison. The reader draws their own conclusion from the evidence.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n500 italic">"If you compare the major bets side by side, you'll notice some give up significantly more than others."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-orange/30 bg-orange/5 p-5 shadow-sm">
        <span class="inline-block text-xs font-heading font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-orange bg-orange/10 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mb-3">Contextual</span>
        <p class="font-heading font-semibold text-navy text-lg mb-2">Japan, communal markets</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n700 mb-3">Information framed through social proof. The reader learns what experienced people already know.</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-n500 italic">"The experienced players at the table know which bets cost the most. Here's what they know."</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>
      All three versions are generous, honest, and non-judgmental. The information is identical. The
      delivery respects the audience's communication expectations.
    </p>
